Software requirements

The Edge System is targeted for operation on resource constrained edge gateway devices that run a variety of Windows and Linux operating systems. Minimum requirements for an edge gateway to host an Edge System are listed below.
Operating systems:
•	Microsoft Windows 10 (64-bit) and higher
•	Ubuntu 16.04 (64-bit) and higher
•	Debian 9
•	Linux on ARM (32)
	
This release might run on other Linux distributions if it meets the requirements for .NET Core on Linux . For more information, see Prerequisites for .NET Core on Windows.
•	Any processor that supports .NET Core 2
•	Docker container compatible

Hardware requirements

•	ARM or Intel CPU
•	1 GHz single core
•	512 MB RAM
•	Internal storage (SSD preferred)
